We are, if those phone calls from the DA haven’t made clear, in the middle of an election campaign. The ANC has been relatively slow to get going this time around, having had other problems to deal with, but things are now moving under a full head of steam. This… In the headlong rush to December’s ANC leadership contest, and the 2019 election that hovers increasingly menacingly after it, the list of casualties is mounting. The naked ambition is leading to the destruction of both pawns and reputations. But in the middle of this something else is happening: truth itself… Land expropriation without compensation is a radical policy stance which the EFF and the ANC are clutching on to like a lifeline in the fight to win back political space and voters ahead of the next election. But, it is also the ANC’s newest lie. By THANDEKA MBABAMA of the…